@nabeel937 That wasn't a solo movie and the critical response to that movie was disastrous effectively ruining the franchise. The final nail in the coffin was the 2017 justice league movie which tanked both critically and commercially.

The new Superman movie is the first entry in a rebooted franchise which has nothing to do with the old timeline other than minor connections to 2022's Suicide Squad and Peacemaker. 

And on top of that, Superman is by far the most recognized superhero in the world along with Spider-Man and Batman. So I'm not surprised if they're starting a new universe with Superman again.
